            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                             \nScrooge thinks that Christmas is a time for paying bills without money, a time for finding yourself a year older and not an hour richer, and a time for balancing your books. He believes that it's a time when \"Want is keenly felt, and Abundance rejoices\" but he doesn't make merry himself at Christmas and can't afford to make idle people merry. He also thinks that those who are badly off must go to establishments that he helps to support, and if they would rather die, they had better do it and decrease the surplus population.\n\nSources:\n  - christmas_carol.txt (https://objectstorage.us-chicago-1.oraclecloud.com/n/orasenatdpltintegration03/b/JoeHahnRagBucket/o/rag/doc/christmas_carol.txt)    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
