          "interpreter" : "script.low",
          "taskStatus" : "SUCCESS",
          "status" : "SUCCESS",
          "results" : [
            {
              "message" : "\nRESPONSE                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                      \nAccording to Charles Dickens' classic novel \"A Christmas Carol\", Ebenezer Scrooge thinks that Christmas is a waste of time and money. He views it as a time when people are foolishly generous and indulgent, and he believes that it's all just a excuse for people to be idle and frivolous.\n\nIn fact, when his nephew Fred invites him to Christmas dinner, Scrooge responds with his famous line: \"Bah! Humbug!\" This phrase has become synonymous with a grumpy or dismissive attitude towards Christmas.\n\nScrooge's negative views on Christmas are largely driven by his own bitter and miserly personality, as well as his painful past experiences. However, as the story unfolds, Scrooge is visited by the Ghosts of Christmas Past, Present, and Yet to Come, who help him to see the error of his ways and ultimately transform his outlook on Christmas and life in general.    \n\n\n---------------------------\n",
              "type" : "TEXT"
            }
          ],
          "forms" : "[]"
